headlines.description: — Terry Rozier and Kelly Oubre Jr. each scored 23 points and the Charlotte Hornets emerged from the All-Star break looking reenergized with a 125-93 rout of the Toronto Raptors on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hornets emerge from break reenergized, rout Raptors 125-93

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Indiana Pacers
San Antonio Spurs at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — Coming off his first All-Star appearance, Dejounte Murray had to work extra hard in the highest-scoring game in the NBA this season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray, Spurs outlast Wizards 157-153 in double overtime

events.name: Miami Heat at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Tyler Herro scored 25 points, Jimmy Butler had 23 and the Miami Heat overcame RJ Barrett's career-high 46 points to beat the New York Knicks 115-100 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat overcome Barrett's career-best 46, beat Knicks 115-100

headlines.description: — James Harden had just hit a stepback 3-pointer while being fouled, a move seen countless times from the 10-time All-Star and 2018 MVP. Joel Embiid, his new teammate, raised both hands and met up with Harden at midcourt for a hug.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harden makes 76ers debut in blowout win over Timberwolves

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — CJ McCollum's still working on his on-court chemistry with Brandon Ingram and the rest of the New Orleans Pelicans.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCollum continues scoring spree, Pelicans top Suns 117-102

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell hit a career-high seven 3-pointers and scored 33 points to help the Utah Jazz beat the Dallas Mavericks 114-109 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell hits 7 3s, scores 33 points in Jazz's win over Mavs

events.name: LA Clippers at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Terance Mann had 19 points and 10 rebounds, Amir Coffey added 12 of his 14 in the fourth quarter and the Los Angeles Clippers returned from the All-Star break with a 105-102 victory over the Los Angeles Lakers on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers edge Lakers 105-102 for 6th straight rivalry win
